  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two diagrams of a brick being dropped from the top of a building. The first diagram is labeled Case A, and shows a brick being dropped from the top of a building toward the concrete ground. The second diagram is labeled Case B, and shows a brick being dropped from the top a building toward a thin foam pad that is lying on the ground.\" src=\"/images/cb20c91fd543316ec25db4e838c12ef6.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A brick is dropped from the top of a building and falls toward the ground. In Case <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span>, the brick lands on concrete and breaks into many pieces. In Case <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span>, the brick lands on a thin foam pad and does not break. Why does the brick not break in Case <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> but breaks in Case <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Because the foam pad reduces the impulse applied to the brick to stop it.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Because the foam pad reduces the work done on the brick to stop it.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Because the foam pad increases the magnitude of the force applied on the brick to stop it.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Because the foam pad increases the time that the force is applied to the brick to stop it.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
